receive nice paychecks.

00:24:03.220 --> 00:24:07.275
Some of us may go onto graduate school,
and receive all right paychecks.

00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:11.700
[LAUGH] And
some of us may take a well-deserved break.

00:24:12.800 --> 00:24:14.920
But what, then?

00:24:15.320 --> 00:24:21.360
Instead of thinking about the next
achievement, now's our opportunity

00:24:21.540 --> 00:24:28.340
to reflect on purpose as we enter
the next stage of our life.

00:24:28.360 --> 00:24:32.620
Purpose, the reason we exist.

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:36.560
Maybe Carnegie Mellon has already
helped you find your purpose.

00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:39.360
Maybe you're just getting started.

00:24:40.180 --> 00:24:44.660
We should reflect on purpose
because it develops us,

00:24:44.660 --> 00:24:49.080
keeps us resilient and
can lead us to happiness.

00:24:50.480 --> 00:24:55.360
So how do we crystallize purpose, or
even find purpose in the first place?

00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:57.560
We help others.

00:24:59.175 --> 00:25:04.180
We are driven by the need
to impact others.

00:25:04.180 --> 00:25:06.300
We're social animals, after all.

00:25:06.300 --> 00:25:09.340
I'm a biology major, trust me.

00:25:09.980 --> 00:25:18.160
So what's the relationship between
purpose, helping others and happiness?

00:25:18.220 --> 00:25:23.760
Well, to me,
there are three levels of happiness.

00:25:24.460 --> 00:25:29.380
First, you can get happiness
from simply building something.

00:25:29.620 --> 00:25:35.560
Then there's a second level of happiness
when people praise what you have built.

00:25:35.560 --> 00:25:39.920
And then there's this
third level of happiness,

00:25:39.920 --> 00:25:46.620
when someone tells you what you
have built has changed my life.

00:25:47.060 --> 00:25:50.960
That level of happiness
just can't be beat.

00:25:50.960 --> 00:25:55.430
And the path that makes you feel
the most fulfilled, the path that

00:25:55.430 --> 00:26:02.500
gives you the greatest happiness,
can give you insight on purpose.

00:26:02.940 --> 00:26:07.980
We've already been practicing,
impacting the lives of others.

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:14.691
We've overloaded, become execs on boards,
volunteered for 1000plus, tutored,

00:26:14.700 --> 00:26:20.900
TAed, researched,
strived because CMU is a striving place.

00:26:21.620 --> 00:26:25.760
We're a bunch of overachievers who've been
presented with so many opportunities,

00:26:25.760 --> 00:26:30.140
and have been encouraged to learn.

00:26:30.280 --> 00:26:35.660
Now's our time to put
practice into action.

00:26:36.500 --> 00:26:39.066
Continue to strive.

00:26:39.066 --> 00:26:41.840
Continue to aspire.

00:26:42.420 --> 00:26:47.996
And as you leave here today,
center your life around purpose.

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:51.240
Center your life around impacting others.

00:26:51.720 --> 00:26:54.620
Let purpose guide you.

00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:58.760
And to everyone who
helped us along the way,

00:26:58.770 --> 00:27:02.662
