01:23:59.800 --> 01:24:02.265
undergraduate students in North America.

01:24:02.265 --> 01:24:05.570
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]
&gt;&gt; Competing

01:24:05.570 --> 01:24:10.000
against the best undergraduate
math students in the country.

01:24:10.260 --> 01:24:11.780
During your time here,

01:24:11.780 --> 01:24:16.340
your accomplishments helped
the University scale new heights.

01:24:16.420 --> 01:24:21.680
Thanks to the generosity of about 450
donors and the efforts of many members

01:24:21.680 --> 01:24:27.140
of the CMU community the last four years
saw a historical buildup of dedicated

01:24:27.140 --> 01:24:32.740
endowment to support students through
presidential fellowships and scholarships.

01:24:32.920 --> 01:24:38.570
This program just established three
years ago has grown to benefit a total

01:24:38.570 --> 01:24:44.440
of 255 students this year in every
college and school at Carnegie Mellon.

01:24:44.500 --> 01:24:49.740
Similar efforts were created to support
faculty through endowed professorships.

01:24:49.740 --> 01:24:54.067
Your ideas and
exuberant engagement helped the University

01:24:54.067 --> 01:24:58.221
establish an historic expansion
of the campus to benefit

01:24:58.221 --> 01:25:02.907
generations of students in teaching,
learning and research.

01:25:02.907 --> 01:25:06.858
All this was fueled by one of the most
sustained and successful fundraising

01:25:06.860 --> 01:25:11.900
efforts in a continuous four-year
period the university has witnessed.

01:25:12.020 --> 01:25:16.340
This happened as the university's
visibility expanded around the world,

01:25:16.340 --> 01:25:21.180
from pioneering university participation
at the Tony Awards on Broadway.

01:25:21.420 --> 01:25:26.470
To faculty engagement at the World
Economic Forum in Davos, to hosting

01:25:26.470 --> 01:25:31.335
the President of the United States on our
campus and to attracting several large

01:25:31.335 --> 01:25:36.230
multi-national companies to Pittsburgh,
while at the same time we nurtured and

01:25:36.230 --> 01:25:41.200
supported our activities at
CMU campuses around the world.

01:25:41.400 --> 01:25:46.060
Your work at the university
community also brought to the fore

01:25:46.060 --> 01:25:51.000
the critical need to enhance
the CMU experience for all.

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:55.520
This commitment has already produced
initiatives and action plans for

01:25:55.520 --> 01:26:00.130
the next several years to improve programs
and infrastructure for counseling,

01:26:00.130 --> 01:26:04.440
mentoring, and
enhancing student support and services.

01:26:04.440 --> 01:26:09.800
We have accomplished all this together
in close partnerships with faculty and

01:26:09.800 --> 01:26:15.540
staff, parents, families, friends,
coaches, trustees, and alumni.

01:26:15.640 --> 01:26:20.060
Today we pause to reflect and
celebrate as well as recognize and

01:26:20.060 --> 01:26:24.540
express our pride in what you have
accomplished in your four years.

01:26:24.540 --> 01:26:32.160
And today, I challenge you again,
what will you do in the next four years?

01:26:32.500 --> 01:26:38.680
As you go out into the world, in whatever
you do as a Carnegie Mellon graduate,

01:26:38.680 --> 01:26:44.240
you have joined over
100,000 living alumni.

01:26:44.240 --> 01:26:48.100
We know that you will be enormously
successful and impactful.

01:26:48.220 --> 01:26:53.800
If history is any indication,
many of you will occupy leadership roles

01:26:53.800 --> 01:26:58.820
where your principles and values will
determine the scale of your impact.

01:26:58.820 --> 01:27:04.380
If you are a change agent, your world
will be changing even faster than

01:27:04.380 --> 01:27:09.420
ever before because of the accelerating
pace of change around the world.

01:27:09.420 --> 01:27:13.700
If you are someone who,
through hard work and aspiration,

01:27:13.700 --> 01:27:18.910
tirelessly seeks to improve status quo,
it is imperative

01:27:18.910 --> 01:27:23.428
that you adhere to your principles
even in the face of obstacles,

01:27:23.428 --> 01:27:29.120
adversity and setbacks,
especially created by those

01:27:29.120 --> 01:27:34.200
who are uncomfortable with the disruptions
that emerge from changing the status quo.

01:27:34.680 --> 01:27:40.340
Rosalynn Carter once said, a leader
takes people where they want to go.

01:27:40.340 --> 01:27:44.080
A great leader takes people
where they ought to go

01:27:44.080 --> 01:27:46.960
even if they do not want to go there.

01:27:47.120 --> 01:27:51.840
Such leaders make great personal
sacrifices to move their organizations or

01:27:51.840 --> 01:27:59.020
their countries to a much higher level,
against incredible odds and opposition.

01:27:59.100 --> 01:28:03.900
You may make some mistakes along
the way but you will learn from it,

01:28:03.901 --> 01:28:06.793
and be a better person,
and a better leader.

01:28:06.800 --> 01:28:10.820
Never be hesitant to voice your opinion.

01:28:11.120 --> 01:28:17.560
Sir Winston Churchill once famously said,
when the eagles are silent,

01:28:17.720 --> 01:28:24.380
the parrots begin to jabber.  Be an eagle, not a parrot.

01:28:24.480 --> 01:28:27.400
Consider the case of Abraham Lincoln,

01:28:27.400 --> 01:28:32.760
who many historians consider the greatest
president of the Untied States.

01:28:32.840 --> 01:28:37.120
Lincoln, who led our country in
the middle of the Civil War,

01:28:37.180 --> 01:28:40.420
established the Morrill Land Grant Act
in 1862,

01:28:40.420 --> 01:28:46.060
that completely transformed the higher
education system of the US.

01:28:46.080 --> 01:28:49.180
His signing of
the Emancipation Proclamation,

01:28:49.180 --> 01:28:54.220
during a bloody Civil War that tore
the country apart, on January 1,

01:28:54.220 --> 01:29:00.540
1863, as a Presidential Executive Order,
changed our society forever.

01:29:00.700 --> 01:29:06.220
Also in 1863, Lincoln established
the National Academy of Sciences,

01:29:06.220 --> 01:29:11.060
with a remarkable vision that
was free of political influence.

01:29:11.140 --> 01:29:16.000
Lincoln faced resistance during
his entire leadership tenure.

01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:19.720
Another iconic leader of
our times penned a speech

01:29:19.720 --> 01:29:24.440
that captures this theme because
of the way it played out.

01:29:24.440 --> 01:29:32.820
As I read this quote, try to guess to whom
it is attributed, the quote goes like this.

01:29:32.920 --> 01:29:37.740
There will always be dissident
voices expressing opposition without

01:29:37.740 --> 01:29:43.060
alternatives, finding fault but
never favor.

01:29:43.140 --> 01:29:49.940
Perceiving gloom on every side and
seeking influence without responsibility.

01:29:50.080 --> 01:29:54.812
That was a speech that
President John F Kennedy was supposed to

01:29:54.812 --> 01:29:58.546
deliver in Dallas on November 22, 1963.

01:29:58.546 --> 01:30:01.645
These words were in his
prepared remarks and

01:30:01.645 --> 01:30:04.752
he never had a chance
to deliver his speech.

01:30:04.760 --> 01:30:09.960
My charge to you is do the right
thing based on principles,

01:30:09.960 --> 01:30:15.980
values, hard work, honesty, and integrity.

01:30:16.060 --> 01:30:20.560
As graduates entering a new world,
facing new challenges,

01:30:20.560 --> 01:30:27.240
it is your duty to ensure that fake
news does not overwhelm truth.

01:30:27.240 --> 01:30:31.020
Noise does not drown out the signal and

01:30:31.020 --> 01:30:36.640
mere superficial style does
not replace deep substance.

01:30:36.680 --> 01:30:41.620
With a CMU degree, you are well
prepared to separate signal from noise,

01:30:41.630 --> 01:30:46.010
fact from fiction, and
evidence from a mere innuendo.

01:30:46.010 --> 01:30:47.480
As you accomplish much,

01:30:47.480 --> 01:30:53.180
we expect you to return to this campus
sharing your knowledge and experiences.

01:30:53.320 --> 01:30:56.200
Whatever you do, wherever you live,

01:30:56.220 --> 01:31:01.540
you will have a profound impact on
the world equipped with a CMU degree.

01:31:01.620 --> 01:31:06.697
I cannot wait to see how you change
the world, you were my freshman class and

01:31:06.697 --> 01:31:11.874
therefore, you are my special class of
students forever, with whom I have bonded.

01:31:11.874 --> 01:31:17.748
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]
&gt;&gt; With whom I have bonded so

01:31:17.748 --> 01:31:22.177
much over the past four years,
I will always be connected with you,

01:31:22.177 --> 01:31:24.833
congratulations, class of 2017.

01:31:24.833 --> 01:31:31.400
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]

01:31:31.400 --> 01:31:34.200
&gt;&gt; We will conclude today's ceremony by

01:31:34.200 --> 01:31:39.050
singing the alma mater by the vocal
performance class of 2017.

01:31:39.050 --> 01:31:40.790
We invite you to please rise and

01:31:40.790 --> 01:31:45.640
sing along, the words to our alma
mater can be found in your program.

01:31:45.640 --> 01:31:48.500
Also, please remain standing at
the conclusion of the alma mater for

01:31:48.500 --> 01:31:51.140
the recession.

